        "paragraph_1": "Irwin's story began in 1885 when Charles Irwin patented the solid-centre auger bit in Wilmington, Ohio — a drill bit design so effective it set the standard for decades. But it was Danish immigrant William Petersen who, in 1924 in DeWitt, Nebraska, invented the locking pliers that would become the brand's most iconic product: the Vise-Grip.",
