    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the history of Irwin Vise-Grip locking pliers?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>Vise-Grip</strong> locking pliers were invented in <strong>1924</strong> by Danish immigrant <strong>William Petersen</strong> in DeWitt, Nebraska. He initially sold them from the boot of his car to farmers and mechanics. In 1934, he formed the Petersen Manufacturing Company, and in 1957 added the easy-release trigger that defines the modern design. After over 100 years, Vise-Grip remains the world's best-selling locking plier.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What types of drill bits does Irwin make?",
            "answer": "<p>Irwin produces a comprehensive range of professional drill bits including <strong>Speedbor</strong> spade bits for fast wood boring, <strong>Unibit</strong> step drills for sheet metal, SDS-Plus masonry bits, multi-material bits, HSS metal bits, and brad-point wood bits. The Speedbor Tri-Flute design clears chips faster and reduces binding in deep holes.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What warranty do Irwin tools carry?",
            "answer": "<p>Irwin hand tools carry a <strong>lifetime warranty</strong> against defects in materials and workmanship under normal use. Power tool accessories such as drill bits and saw blades are warranted against manufacturing defects. As an official UK stockist, Invicta Tools can process warranty claims directly on your behalf.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between Vise-Grip and standard locking pliers?",
            "answer": "<p><strong>Vise-Grip</strong> is the original locking plier — invented by William Petersen and refined continuously for over 100 years. The key differences are the precision-machined turn-screw adjustment, hardened alloy steel jaws that grip without slipping, and the patented easy-release trigger. Many brands imitate the design, but Vise-Grip remains the trade standard for a reason.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who owns Irwin Tools?",
            "answer": "<p>Irwin is owned by <strong>Stanley Black & Decker</strong>, who acquired the brand in 2017. The Irwin brand portfolio includes Vise-Grip, Quick-Grip, Speedbor, Marathon, Marples and Unibit — each a category leader. The brand traces its origins to <strong>1885</strong> when Charles Irwin patented the solid-centre auger bit in Ohio.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Irwin?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Irwin range including Vise-Grip, Quick-Grip and Speedbor products. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. We also provide free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
